7
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:55,500
[Su Yun]

8
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,110
Hello?

9
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,670
Thrombus secondary to left ventricle?

10
00:02:04,670 --> 00:02:05,750
Is surgery needed?

11
00:02:05,910 --> 00:02:06,440
Yes.

12
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:07,990
How much is it?

13
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:09,760
After reimbursement
under the New Rural Health Insurance,

14
00:02:09,760 --> 00:02:10,520
50,000.

15
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:13,480
Yeah, it'll come out of your paycheck.

16
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:14,780
Hua.

17
00:02:14,780 --> 00:02:16,080
I'm your nephew.

18
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:16,870
No nonsense.

19
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:18,990
Even nephews need
to bill calculated clearly.

20
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:27,390
Then I'll deduct it
from Zheng Ren's salary.

21
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:28,990
Deduct it from Zheng Ren's salary?

22
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:30,590
Do you think

23
00:02:30,590 --> 00:02:31,590
he still has wages to deduct?

24
00:02:31,830 --> 00:02:32,600
Do you know

25
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:33,920
how much money I've spent on him?

26
00:02:34,150 --> 00:02:35,390
Anyway, you guys figure it out.

27
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:36,800
There's no way I'm doing the surgery

28
00:02:36,830 --> 00:02:37,670
for free.

29
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:39,320
Fine, Hua.

30
00:02:39,590 --> 00:02:41,150
Then deduct it from Zheng Ren's salary.

31
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:42,110
Love you.

32
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:47,670
The money problem was solved.

33
00:02:48,830 --> 00:02:49,360
We have a sponsor.

34
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:52,110
Thank you, Doctor.

35
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:53,320
Get some rest.

36
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:54,870
Thanks!

37
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:56,590
- Go through treatment with peace.
- Thanks!

38
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,640
- Thanks!
- Thanks!

39
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:02,270
That went so well.

40
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:03,710
Nothing goes wrong

41
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:04,640
when I'm doing it.

42
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:11,180
[Crossed]

43
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:15,080
I'll continue after a meal.

44
00:03:17,110 --> 00:03:17,590
Come in.

45
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:21,200
Hello, Dr. Lin.

46
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:22,760
Sorry for adding your number.

47
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,150
But I'm not here to see a doctor.

48
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:26,150
There's something I'd like to tell you.

49
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,250
These

50
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,640
are our new products.

51
00:03:38,980 --> 00:03:40,820
[Emergency Office]

52
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:41,960
Tao.

53
00:03:42,390 --> 00:03:43,500
I heard the doctor returned from Man'ou

54
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:44,960
diagnosed a diarrhea patient today.

55
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,920
It was identified
as travelers' diarrhea.

56
00:03:47,430 --> 00:03:48,540
Diarrhea is a symptom

57
00:03:48,550 --> 00:03:49,960
that can be triggered by many factors.

58
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:51,960
Yeah.

59
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,280
The people must think diarrhea

60
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,550
is a minor problem.

61
00:03:54,830 --> 00:03:55,710
But trying to pinpoint the cause

62
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:56,520
of the diagnosis

63
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:57,920
has been difficult for doctors.

64
00:03:58,920 --> 00:03:59,590
The same diarrhea

65
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,200
was cured for less than one yuan.

66
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,920
But Yun needs 50,000.

67
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:05,550
Life isn't fair.

68
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:13,830
But

69
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,550
it's a blessing to be able to pinpoint

70
00:04:15,710 --> 00:04:17,320
the cause of the diagnosis.

71
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:18,350
So kids,

72
00:04:18,790 --> 00:04:19,590
be sure to keep working

73
00:04:19,710 --> 00:04:20,470
and learning

74
00:04:20,590 --> 00:04:21,440
in real-life practice!

75
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,910
Move closer to Yun.

76
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:23,390
This way,

77
00:04:23,390 --> 00:04:24,350
we can hope to be the pride

78
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,080
of Haicheng...

79
00:04:32,350 --> 00:04:33,470
Less talking, more work.

80
00:04:40,910 --> 00:04:41,760
You did this, Hua?

81
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:43,830
What?

82
00:04:44,150 --> 00:04:44,760
Take a look.

83
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:49,700
["Half a yuan to solve patient's
struggle for five years]

84
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,700
[-Talented female doctor who returned
from Man'ou"]

85
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:51,760
Not bad.

86
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,590
What?

87
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:53,440
Scroll down.

88
00:04:53,590 --> 00:04:54,680
Look at the comment with the most likes.

89
00:04:57,150 --> 00:04:58,880
The same diarrhea for five years.

90
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,760
Some doctors charge half a yuan,

91
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:02,520
and some charge 50,000.

92
00:05:03,590 --> 00:05:05,910
It's true that the Haicheng Hospital
is a mixed bag.

93
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,000
Some of the doctors are good.

94
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,440
Some are pretty dumb.

95
00:05:08,710 --> 00:05:09,760
Like the one
from the Emergency Department.

96
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:11,320
Have you heard

97
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:12,590
of the legendary doctor?

98
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:14,120
Yes.

99
00:05:14,390 --> 00:05:16,080
There was a doctor there
by the name of Su.

100
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,470
Everything cost the patient

101
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:19,520
thousands.

102
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:21,320
Check from head to toe.

103
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,790
When he couldn't diagnose it,

104
00:05:22,790 --> 00:05:24,790
he pushed it to rheumatology.

105
00:05:25,590 --> 00:05:27,080
Unscrupulous, black-hearted doctor!

106
00:05:27,270 --> 00:05:29,440
But I heard he was very handsome.

107
00:05:29,580 --> 00:05:30,620
[Unscrupulous, black-hearted doctor!
But I heard he was very handsome.]

108
00:05:32,830 --> 00:05:33,760
You're still laughing?

109
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,350
One is a common parasitic infection.

110
00:05:35,470 --> 00:05:36,880
Another one is Loeffler endocarditis.

111
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:37,640
It's not the same.

112
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:39,320
I'm not the one who did it.

113
00:05:41,590 --> 00:05:42,960
Then the doctor returned
from Man'ou must have done it.

114
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:44,590
I can't tell

115
00:05:44,790 --> 00:05:45,960
that she's so calculating.

116
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,680
Don't blame it on Man'ou.

117
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:49,450
She belongs to Haicheng Hospital now.

118
00:05:49,790 --> 00:05:50,280
Hua.

119
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:51,820
I'm your nephew.

120
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,150
My own nephew,

121
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:54,880
who's been giving me trouble.

122
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,470
Provocation?

123
00:05:56,710 --> 00:05:57,640
It doesn't work for me.

124
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:06,760
I'll get back to work then.

125
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:13,500
Don't you like spicy food?

126
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:18,780
This way.

127
00:06:18,780 --> 00:06:19,550
Add some noodles.

128
00:06:22,230 --> 00:06:22,880
Delivery!

129
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:24,880
Is No. 31 done?

130
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:25,680
Almost there.

131
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:26,640
- Alright.
- Tianshui.

132
00:06:26,910 --> 00:06:27,320
Xia.

133
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:28,760
You're running out of breath.

134
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:29,470
You're so hardworking.

135
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:30,440
How many orders did you do?

136
00:06:30,710 --> 00:06:31,390
Almost 30.

137
00:06:31,470 --> 00:06:32,440
Almost 30?

138
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:33,150
Awesome.

139
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:35,270
Are you saving up for getting married?

140
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,200
I'm still single.

141
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,120
I'll be going now.

142
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:38,590
Alright.

143
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:43,470
Tianshui!

144
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:45,880
What's wrong with you, Tianshui?

145
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:47,710
- Tianshui!
- What's wrong?

146
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:48,470
I don't know.

147
00:06:48,470 --> 00:06:49,120
I'll take a look.

148
00:06:49,590 --> 00:06:50,150
Hello?

149
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:51,200
Hello?

150
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,320
Call the ambulance. Hurry!

151
00:06:56,620 --> 00:06:57,320
Alright.

152
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:07,080
What are you doing here?

153
00:07:08,230 --> 00:07:09,120
Does he faint often?

154
00:07:10,350 --> 00:07:11,960
I heard him say he fainted before.

155
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,000
I think he had a check-up.

156
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,440
Said it was kidney failure.

157
00:07:14,790 --> 00:07:15,350
Impossible.

158
00:07:15,470 --> 00:07:16,150
Kidney failure that can lead

159
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:16,960
to fainting

160
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:17,910
will have complications

161
00:07:18,030 --> 00:07:19,270
such as edema and anuria.

162
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:19,960
Moreover,

163
00:07:20,150 --> 00:07:21,120
Syncope isn't the main mode

164
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:21,880
of kidney failure either.

165
00:07:22,390 --> 00:07:23,150
The report's out.

166
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:29,080
Maybe I should read it.

167
00:07:31,270 --> 00:07:32,350
Diagnosed as an ionic disorder.

168
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:32,830
Potassium ion

169
00:07:32,830 --> 00:07:33,270
2.2 milli (millimoles per liter)

170
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,080
Should we treat him

171
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:34,680
with potassium ion supplementation?

172
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,230
- No need.
- No need.

173
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,350
Low potassium has nothing

174
00:07:36,350 --> 00:07:37,000
to do with syncope.

175
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,590
Do you usually have violent vomiting

176
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:39,520
or diarrhea?

177
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:42,520
I've had occasional diarrhea
for over a year.

178
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:43,880
But no vomiting.

179
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:45,120
Are you eating properly?

180
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:46,910
Kind of normal, I suppose.

181
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:48,680
There's still a lot of tests to be done.

182
00:07:48,910 --> 00:07:49,910
Let's transfer to urology first.

183
00:07:50,230 --> 00:07:51,680
Why? Just do it here.

184
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:53,560
Can I not stay in the hospital?

185
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:54,470
Not possible.

186
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:55,960
The cause is still unknown.

187
00:07:56,030 --> 00:07:57,150
But ionic disorders

188
00:07:57,270 --> 00:07:58,350
are serious enough to kill.

189
00:07:59,230 --> 00:08:00,120
Tianshui,

190
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,390
then I think you should listen

191
00:08:01,470 --> 00:08:02,350
to the doctors.

192
00:08:02,910 --> 00:08:03,910
It's important to earn money.

193
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:05,350
But your health is more important.

194
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:06,760
Stay in the hospital for now.

195
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:09,590
Alright.

196
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,710
The cause is still unclear.

197
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:12,640
How about doing a check-up

198
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:13,680
and finding out the cause?

199
00:08:13,710 --> 00:08:14,960
- Do it!
- Do it!

200
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:16,350
Yes.

201
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,830
Insufficient body fluids...

202
00:08:28,390 --> 00:08:30,350
[Nursing Record Sheet]
Yesterday's rehydration to now

203
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:31,910
was over 2,000 milliliters.

204
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:34,110
How could he not have enough fluids?

205
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,320
And he can eat, too.

206
00:08:40,870 --> 00:08:41,440
You're dealing with Chang Feng's

207
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,320
medical representative?

208
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:45,990
Mr. Lin.

209
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:47,750
Knock before entering.

210
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:48,920
Don't you have any manners?

211
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,320
Someone saw

212
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:55,560
the Chang Feng's medical representative

213
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:56,470
enter your consulting room.

214
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,350
What did she offer you?

215
00:08:58,800 --> 00:08:59,680
Did you say yes to everything?

216
00:09:02,350 --> 00:09:02,960
Answer me.

217
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:08,710
Why would I say yes?

218
00:09:09,470 --> 00:09:10,320
You've been following me

219
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:11,510
at the hospital since you were a kid.

220
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,080
You've seen a few of my peers

221
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,040
fall from grace.

222
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,320
Some even went to jail.

223
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,160
Have you forgotten?

224
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:17,990
Hanging out
with a medical representative

225
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,470
is a recipe for disaster.

226
00:09:21,990 --> 00:09:23,230
I remember those who had dealings

227
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:24,040
with the medical representative

228
00:09:24,110 --> 00:09:25,040
didn't end well.

229
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:26,400
I also remember someone changed

230
00:09:26,470 --> 00:09:27,200
my choice of college application

231
00:09:27,230 --> 00:09:28,620
without permission and I almost
couldn't study medicine.

232
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:29,630
Which one do you think

233
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,320
is really ruining my career?

234
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,230
I hope you realize

235
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:37,710
the days of asking for your approval

236
00:09:37,870 --> 00:09:38,870
for everything in the name

237
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:40,200
of what's best for me

238
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,320
are well behind us.

239
00:09:42,470 --> 00:09:42,960
If you think my dealings

240
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,080
with the medical representative

241
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,040
are detrimental
to the hospital's interests,

242
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:46,750
then report me to the president.

243
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:48,510
If there's nothing else,

244
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:49,470
I'm going to see my patient,

245
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:50,510
Mr. Lin.

246
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:09,800
Mr. Peng.

247
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:12,110
Yun.

248
00:10:12,990 --> 00:10:13,870
Long time no see.

249
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:14,640
Long time no see.

250
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:15,790
Don't you drink coffee lately?

251
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,230
I wouldn't dare drink it.

252
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:17,990
Take a seat.

253
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:20,510
If it wasn't for you guys,

254
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:21,870
I'd be done.

255
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:23,960
I see you've done a good job

256
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:24,710
with your website.

257
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:25,990
Passable.

258
00:10:26,230 --> 00:10:27,590
I guess we're on the right track.

259
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,320
The average number
of people online is 3000.

260
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:30,630
At this rate,

261
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:32,510
live surgery is just around the corner.

262
00:10:32,990 --> 00:10:33,960
Live surgery?

263
00:10:34,990 --> 00:10:35,470
Yeah.

264
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,440
With the advent of the 5G era,

265
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:38,280
you can watch

266
00:10:38,510 --> 00:10:39,470
and learn

267
00:10:39,590 --> 00:10:41,400
from top doctors' surgery procedures
without stepping outside.

268
00:10:41,870 --> 00:10:43,160
Doctors can remotely direct

269
00:10:43,470 --> 00:10:45,560
cross-regional surgeries
through remote guidance.

270
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,960
Technology changes the future.

271
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:52,440
And what we want to do here

272
00:10:52,870 --> 00:10:54,320
is to find the pioneer.

273
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:55,440
Then who is the pioneer?

274
00:10:55,830 --> 00:10:56,400
Dr. Zheng.

275
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:00,630
Don't get any ideas about him.

276
00:11:01,630 --> 00:11:03,350
But that's what he proposed.

277
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:04,800
Zheng Ren?

278
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,110
Does he want to do live surgery?

279
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:07,920
Yeah.

280
00:11:08,590 --> 00:11:09,960
I think he's a visionary.

281
00:11:13,350 --> 00:11:13,920
By the way,

282
00:11:14,510 --> 00:11:15,510
why did you come to see me?

283
00:11:18,470 --> 00:11:19,110
I've got a job for you.

284
00:11:34,980 --> 00:11:37,500
[Ultrasonographic diagnosis of conjoined
twins with multiple deformities case]

285
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:44,900
[A case of organogenesis in a conjoined
infant diagnosed by spiral CT]

286
00:12:10,220 --> 00:12:11,660
[Great arteries complete transposition
with abnormal pulmonary arteries infant]

287
00:12:11,660 --> 00:12:13,100
[In development, constantly drains blood
from abnormal fetuses that lack a heart]

288
00:12:20,470 --> 00:12:20,960
